.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH exists 1  "exists " 
.SH NAME
exists \- Check if a file exists and return its location
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBexists\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIPATH\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Check if a file exists and return its location
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIPATH\fR>
Path within the share (format: [context:]path)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
    nofs exists media:/photos/pic.jpg      # Check if file exists
    nofs exists media:/docs/missing.txt    # Returns error if not found

EXIT CODES:
    0 \- File exists
    1 \- File does not exist

OUTPUT:
    Prints the branch path containing the file if it exists.
